2. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes a new data structure for low stretch under adversarial attack, which is a key topic in this sub-category. 
3. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with peer-to-peer networks and their resilience to attacks, which is a topic within this sub-category. 
4. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper deals with the structure and resilience of peer-to-peer networks, which is a topic within this sub-category. 
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper deals with adversarial attacks on networks and proposes a self-healing algorithm, which is a topic within this sub-category.
